---
# Static analysis policy. Enforced as a CI gate.
#
# The policy keeps the high-value check families on by default (bugprone, concurrency,
# cppcoreguidelines, modernize, performance, portability, readability) and disables
# only the specific checks that do not apply to this codebase. Every disabled check is
# listed below with its reason so the policy stays auditable rather than a blanket
# opt-out. The remaining enabled checks pass cleanly across the whole tree.
#
# Disabled, grouped by reason:
#
#   Not satisfiable with the standard library alone (would require the GSL, which the
#   project deliberately does not depend on):
#     * cppcoreguidelines-pro-bounds-constant-array-index  (wants gsl::at)
#     * cppcoreguidelines-pro-bounds-pointer-arithmetic    (C/POSIX API boundaries)
#     * cppcoreguidelines-pro-bounded-array-to-pointer-decay
#     * cppcoreguidelines-owning-memory                    (wants gsl::owner)
#
#   Intentional low-level realtime / POSIX code (RealtimeManager stack/heap prefault,
#   SignalHandler signalfd/ppoll structs, PiMutex's pthread_mutex_t). Using containers
#   or smart pointers here would defeat the page-faulting/locking purpose, and the C
#   structs are populated field-by-field or by syscalls:
#     * cppcoreguidelines-no-malloc
#     * cppcoreguidelines-avoid-c-arrays
#     * modernize-avoid-c-arrays
#     * cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-member-init
#     * concurrency-mt-unsafe                  (mallopt runs before any thread starts, D2)
#     * bugprone-implicit-widening-of-multiplication-result  (constexpr byte literals)
#
#   Conflict with deliberate, documented design or value-semantics conventions:
#     * readability-convert-member-functions-to-static  (DSP stages composed by value)
#     * readability-redundant-member-init               (defensive value-initialization)
#     * modernize-use-default-member-init
#     * cppcoreguidelines-use-default-member-init
#     * performance-move-const-arg                      (by-value sink-parameter idiom)
#     * cppcoreguidelines-missing-std-forward           (visitor invoked once per loop item)
#     * cppcoreguidelines-special-member-functions      (move-only compile-anchor helper)
#     * modernize-return-braced-init-list               (explicit return types preferred)
#     * performance-enum-size                           (domain enums; int base intended)
#
#   High false-positive rate in this codebase:
#     * bugprone-unchecked-optional-access     (getter-returned optionals; custom asserts)
#     * bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters   (constructor dependency injection)
#
#   Stylistic, intentionally not enforced:
#     * modernize-use-trailing-return-type
#     * readability-identifier-length
#     * cppcoreguidelines-avoid-magic-numbers / readability-magic-numbers
Checks: >
  -*,
  bugprone-*,
  concurrency-*,
  cppcoreguidelines-*,
  modernize-*,
  performance-*,
  portability-*,
  readability-*,
  -modernize-use-trailing-return-type,
  -readability-identifier-length,
  -cppcoreguidelines-avoid-magic-numbers,
  -readability-magic-numbers,
  -cppcoreguidelines-pro-bounded-array-to-pointer-decay,
  -cppcoreguidelines-pro-bounds-constant-array-index,
  -cppcoreguidelines-pro-bounds-pointer-arithmetic,
  -cppcoreguidelines-owning-memory,
  -cppcoreguidelines-no-malloc,
  -cppcoreguidelines-avoid-c-arrays,
  -modernize-avoid-c-arrays,
  -cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-member-init,
  -concurrency-mt-unsafe,
  -bugprone-implicit-widening-of-multiplication-result,
  -readability-convert-member-functions-to-static,
  -readability-redundant-member-init,
  -modernize-use-default-member-init,
  -cppcoreguidelines-use-default-member-init,
  -performance-move-const-arg,
  -cppcoreguidelines-missing-std-forward,
  -cppcoreguidelines-special-member-functions,
  -modernize-return-braced-init-list,
  -performance-enum-size,
  -bugprone-unchecked-optional-access,
  -bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters

WarningsAsErrors: '*'
HeaderFilterRegex: '.*/(include/radar|src|tests)/.*'
FormatStyle: file
...
